00:44:18.300 --> 00:44:23.100
And they pick up the champagne,
and then they started talking.

00:44:23.100 --> 00:44:26.550
Like, you know, wow,
just unbelievable.

00:44:26.550 --> 00:44:31.680
So we really engaged
them into conversation.

00:44:31.680 --> 00:44:33.060
Talked about nutrition.

00:44:33.060 --> 00:44:34.170
Talked about exercise.

00:44:34.170 --> 00:44:37.980
How you actually do this so
your joints and everything

00:44:37.980 --> 00:44:42.180
stays really healthy
and not being injured.

00:44:42.180 --> 00:44:45.960
And then we got a lot of
tips how microprogression

00:44:45.960 --> 00:44:48.630
could work, and how
with age, you actually

00:44:48.630 --> 00:44:51.260
adapt yourself to it.

00:44:51.260 --> 00:44:52.327
Beautiful.

00:44:52.327 --> 00:44:54.660
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: So I want
to encourage people to start

00:44:54.660 --> 00:44:55.770
thinking about questions.

00:44:55.770 --> 00:44:57.170
We have a mic over there.

