We'll have about five
minutes for questions.

00:45:00.360 --> 00:45:05.100
I just want to ask a
few more questions.

00:45:05.100 --> 00:45:08.910
Being able to stick to this
and accessibility for anyone,

00:45:08.910 --> 00:45:11.280
is microprogressions
the key that

00:45:11.280 --> 00:45:16.500
makes this so addictive
and consistent?

00:45:16.500 --> 00:45:19.700
How does it work that
not only athletes,

00:45:19.700 --> 00:45:22.110
but normal people can--

00:45:22.110 --> 00:45:23.670
or even people
with cerebral palsy

00:45:23.670 --> 00:45:26.260
who can adhere to a
program like this?

00:45:26.260 --> 00:45:29.460
JERZY GREGOREK: So when
we have certain weaknesses

00:45:29.460 --> 00:45:31.680
that we want to
correct, and then we

00:45:31.680 --> 00:45:35.460
have the plan and
strategies-- so The Happy Body

00:45:35.460 --> 00:45:36.600
is that plan and strategy.

00:45:36.600 --> 00:45:39.930
Something else comes up,
which is ability to apply.

00:45:39.930 --> 00:45:43.230
And that ability to apply,
we dealt with in the last 10

00:45:43.230 --> 00:45:45.210
years, after
publishing the book,

00:45:45.210 --> 00:45:47.190
how to actually make it happen.

00:45:47.190 --> 00:45:53.100
During this time, I
talked to my clients a lot

00:45:53.100 --> 00:45:59.520
about Plato and horses and
our emotions and the mind.

00:45:59.520 --> 00:46:01.200
How that plays.

00:46:01.200 --> 00:46:04.140
And then he gave us
a really great image.

00:46:04.140 --> 00:46:08.040
He said, imagine that
your chariot is your body,

00:46:08.040 --> 00:46:11.970
and the horses are your
feelings, emotions.

00:46:11.970 --> 00:46:14.580
And the mind is the rider.

00:46:14.580 --> 00:46:16.770
He said that when the
horses are dragging

00:46:16.770 --> 00:46:19.740
the rider against his
will, danger is coming.

00:46:19.740 --> 00:46:21.220
So that's where
addictions happen

00:46:21.220 --> 00:46:23.400
and all problems and so on.

00:46:23.400 --> 00:46:27.250
So I thought about
this a long time.

00:46:27.250 --> 00:46:30.270
And we focused for
about six, seven years

00:46:30.270 --> 00:46:32.370
of controlling those horses.

00:46:32.370 --> 00:46:36.150
But whenever you control the
horses, something else happens.

00:46:36.150 --> 00:46:40.620
It's that we don't like it,
so we start being against it,

00:46:40.620 --> 00:46:42.800
and we jump back.

00:46:42.800 --> 00:46:47.190
And so how do you actually--

00:46:47.190 --> 00:46:50.620
what do you do with the horses?

00:46:50.620 --> 00:46:55.170
And I came out with the
idea that these horses

00:46:55.170 --> 00:46:58.020
have to be befriended.

00:46:58.020 --> 00:47:02.010
So you work with
poetry and stories

00:47:02.010 --> 00:47:06.120
and then talk to people
around, and you change, slowly,

00:47:06.120 --> 00:47:11.910
the brain patterns that those
horses are aligned with,

00:47:11.910 --> 00:47:14.100
whatever the mind wants.

00:47:14.100 --> 00:47:17.190
So at the beginning,
when something is hard,

00:47:17.190 --> 00:47:20.880
when you want to do
something, and it's good,

00:47:20.880 --> 00:47:24.240
you will not like it usually,
because it takes-- energy

00:47:24.240 --> 00:47:27.780
takes practice, like you said.

00:47:27.780 --> 00:47:30.570
But when you keep
doing at the beginning,

00:47:30.570 --> 00:47:31.980
you are like a stoic.

00:47:31.980 --> 00:47:33.630
You want to control something.

00:47:33.630 --> 00:47:37.090
But if you want to control
something that is difficult,

00:47:37.090 --> 00:47:37.920
it's hard.

00:47:37.920 --> 00:47:41.340
Then you will be not liking it.

00:47:41.340 --> 00:47:48.570
So you can achieve it, but
you will be more resistant,

00:47:48.570 --> 00:47:50.320
and you will not be happy.

00:47:50.320 --> 00:47:53.280
But when you switch,
actually, to the other side,

00:47:53.280 --> 00:47:54.840
then you become this--

00:47:54.840 --> 00:47:57.245
I call it a happy
stoic, the happy stoic.

00:47:57.245 --> 00:48:02.310
The happy stoic is the one that
is aligned with what is good,

00:48:02.310 --> 00:48:05.880
what needs to be improved,
and actually likes it.

00:48:05.880 --> 00:48:08.460
So this is the example.

00:48:08.460 --> 00:48:10.020
I notice over and
over that's what

00:48:10.020 --> 00:48:12.690
happens with losing weight.

00:48:12.690 --> 00:48:18.880
Somebody is 160 pounds and
loses weight, becomes 120.

00:48:18.880 --> 00:48:23.980
But if the brain doesn't
shift, the person stays at 160.

00:48:23.980 --> 00:48:25.780
The brain is in 160.

00:48:25.780 --> 00:48:28.120
The body is in 120.

00:48:28.120 --> 00:48:32.530
And if the brain is not
shifted, then the brain

00:48:32.530 --> 00:48:36.190
will take back the body to 160.

00:48:36.190 --> 00:48:37.590
That's the lifestyle.

00:48:37.590 --> 00:48:41.290
And that is, here,
extremely important

00:48:41.290 --> 00:48:45.590
work that takes the
person from a certain body

00:48:45.590 --> 00:48:48.610
weight to the other
side and creates

00:48:48.610 --> 00:48:56.050
this likability and changes
the whole living system,

00:48:56.050 --> 00:48:59.460
that you become, the
person becomes 120,

00:48:59.460 --> 00:49:02.010
and the brain becomes--
they start liking it.

00:49:02.010 --> 00:49:06.700
And it takes time,
but once it happens,

00:49:06.700 --> 00:49:10.380
the happy story becomes.

00:49:10.380 --> 00:49:16.660
So for us, the recent theory
is that we like dance,

00:49:16.660 --> 00:49:19.950
and we pick up this three
months, four months,

00:49:19.950 --> 00:49:22.780
our next thing--

00:49:22.780 --> 00:49:25.120
120 brain.

00:49:25.120 --> 00:49:26.770
You have the metaphor for it.

00:49:26.770 --> 00:49:32.110
So we go, and we learn dancing
and so on, and it takes heart,

00:49:32.110 --> 00:49:35.820
but in some years,
we'll be dancers.

00:49:35.820 --> 00:49:36.390
Yeah?

00:49:36.390 --> 00:49:37.000
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: Awesome.

00:49:37.000 --> 00:49:39.208
I want to make sure we have
time for a few questions,

00:49:39.208 --> 00:49:42.790
so I'll repeat them if you
can't make your way to the mic.

00:49:42.790 --> 00:49:44.780
So any questions for Jerzy?

