Yes.

00:49:45.280 --> 00:49:46.446
AUDIENCE: I have a question.

00:49:46.446 --> 00:49:52.660
So when you presented that
singular exercise, the flow,

00:49:52.660 --> 00:49:57.088
and you demonstrated that, if a
person starts at a place where

00:49:57.088 --> 00:50:01.762
you actually couldn't completely
do that exercise perfectly, do

00:50:01.762 --> 00:50:03.484
they just keep--

00:50:03.484 --> 00:50:05.944
is your strategy keep
doing that exercise,

00:50:05.944 --> 00:50:08.404
and you will get
better, or should you

00:50:08.404 --> 00:50:11.848
do something else complementary
to increase flexibility

00:50:11.848 --> 00:50:14.074
before you do that exercise?

00:50:14.074 --> 00:50:16.240
JERZY GREGOREK: So what we
do is make a progression.

00:50:16.240 --> 00:50:21.160
So we set up the levels
of squatting to work.

00:50:21.160 --> 00:50:23.710
So you find the
person when the person

00:50:23.710 --> 00:50:26.540
is with dumbbells up
and squatting down.

00:50:26.540 --> 00:50:29.980
So when it comes to the point
when the heel is going up,

00:50:29.980 --> 00:50:34.240
or the body leans forward,
you measure that level

00:50:34.240 --> 00:50:38.960
and sit toward that level.

00:50:38.960 --> 00:50:42.040
And then when you
find that level,

00:50:42.040 --> 00:50:46.120
then you train until that
level becomes comfortable.

00:50:46.120 --> 00:50:50.260
And then you say, one inch
lower, one inch lower.

00:50:50.260 --> 00:50:52.780
Two weeks, three weeks, four
weeks, five weeks, and you're

00:50:52.780 --> 00:50:57.250
slowly, slowly going down
and down until you recover,

00:50:57.250 --> 00:51:01.660
completely, flexibility for
that particular exercise,

00:51:01.660 --> 00:51:02.500
like Power Tower.

00:51:02.500 --> 00:51:04.084
AUDIENCE: So it is
the same exercises.

00:51:04.084 --> 00:51:05.500
JERZY GREGOREK:
The same exercise.

00:51:05.500 --> 00:51:06.580
AUDIENCE: You progress.

00:51:06.580 --> 00:51:07.746
JERZY GREGOREK: Yes, within.

00:51:07.746 --> 00:51:10.500
So you train it like
doing pole vaulting.

00:51:10.500 --> 00:51:12.260
You are a pole vaulter, here.

00:51:12.260 --> 00:51:18.490
You Power Tower, so you
work with one exercise.

00:51:18.490 --> 00:51:23.050
So we can do with
you just short thing.

00:51:23.050 --> 00:51:25.330
You can stand up
and test yourself,

00:51:25.330 --> 00:51:28.250
whether you can go
down toward the chair.

00:51:28.250 --> 00:51:29.170
Stand up, please.

00:51:29.170 --> 00:51:31.660
And then you will see
if you can do that.

00:51:31.660 --> 00:51:36.820
And put your arms on your
chest and try to sit back.

00:51:36.820 --> 00:51:42.040
Sit back and see if you can sit
back without leaning forward.

00:51:42.040 --> 00:51:45.070
So you can see that at a certain
moment you just lean forward.

00:51:45.070 --> 00:51:50.830
And that is the moment that
you need to start working with.

00:51:50.830 --> 00:51:51.970
You see it.

00:51:51.970 --> 00:51:55.270
And mostly we just
squat that way

00:51:55.270 --> 00:52:01.880
and not using our hamstrings
and hips and other joints.

00:52:01.880 --> 00:52:03.530
BRADLEY HOROWITZ:
So that question

00:52:03.530 --> 00:52:04.988
was great, because
it really helped

00:52:04.988 --> 00:52:08.090
me understand that one of
the bases of your system

00:52:08.090 --> 00:52:10.970
is that anyone can do it.

00:52:10.970 --> 00:52:14.180
It's a question of degree,
like you said before.

00:52:14.180 --> 00:52:17.990
And you can do this
right and then continue

00:52:17.990 --> 00:52:21.530
with microprogressions
to achieve more and more.

00:52:21.530 --> 00:52:24.860
So from day one, you can
actually do the exercise.

00:52:24.860 --> 00:52:27.500
I just did it, I
think, part of it.

00:52:27.500 --> 00:52:29.840
And then it's a question
of applying yourself

00:52:29.840 --> 00:52:31.920
and continuing to get
better and better.

00:52:31.920 --> 00:52:34.100
JERZY GREGOREK: So
the whole system

00:52:34.100 --> 00:52:39.270
is built to restore a person
from the level the person is.

00:52:39.270 --> 00:52:41.150
So if you find
yourself-- there are

00:52:41.150 --> 00:52:44.360
five levels for every exercise.

00:52:44.360 --> 00:52:47.540
So if you find yourself
in one exercise level five

00:52:47.540 --> 00:52:52.800
or another one level one, so
you work with those levels,

00:52:52.800 --> 00:52:55.890
and when time passes,
you will become better.

00:52:55.890 --> 00:52:57.860
It's a lot of data
too, because you

00:52:57.860 --> 00:53:00.350
are creating the same
routine, and you're

00:53:00.350 --> 00:53:01.910
doing the same routine.

00:53:01.910 --> 00:53:04.280
And because of it,
you start really

00:53:04.280 --> 00:53:07.190
learning about what you do.

00:53:07.190 --> 00:53:10.910
And then the data
you collect, you

00:53:10.910 --> 00:53:13.670
are learning also
about how to adapt

00:53:13.670 --> 00:53:17.270
that training system in
case something happens.

00:53:17.270 --> 00:53:20.330
So you learn how to
increase the weight.

00:53:20.330 --> 00:53:24.410
You learn how to increase
the depth squatting,

00:53:24.410 --> 00:53:26.380
or you increase the speed.

00:53:26.380 --> 00:53:31.040
And you start really working
on becoming this self coach.

00:53:31.040 --> 00:53:33.980
And after a while, because
you are doing over and over

00:53:33.980 --> 00:53:36.920
the same routine,
you actually learn.

00:53:36.920 --> 00:53:38.184
You have the opportunity to--

00:53:38.184 --> 00:53:39.600
BRADLEY HOROWITZ:
It's a framework

00:53:39.600 --> 00:53:41.320
Googlers would
like, because it's

00:53:41.320 --> 00:53:43.160
an experimental framework
with one variable

00:53:43.160 --> 00:53:44.620
that you can measure, and--

00:53:44.620 --> 00:53:47.510
JERZY GREGOREK: Oh, the tech
generations and all the tech

00:53:47.510 --> 00:53:49.160
people will love The Happy Body.

00:53:49.160 --> 00:53:50.870
Because they love the science.

00:53:50.870 --> 00:53:53.720
Everything is science
in The Happy Body,

00:53:53.720 --> 00:53:56.570
whether it is flexibility,
whether it is strength,

00:53:56.570 --> 00:53:59.990
whether it is ideal body
weight, whether it is leanness,

00:53:59.990 --> 00:54:01.550
everything is in numbers.

00:54:01.550 --> 00:54:03.660
It's mathematics all of it.

00:54:03.660 --> 00:54:07.970
So because it's mathematics,
tech people and engineers

00:54:07.970 --> 00:54:08.470
love it.

00:54:08.470 --> 00:54:10.055
They say, oh, I love it.

00:54:10.055 --> 00:54:11.420
Oh, yes.

00:54:11.420 --> 00:54:13.820
And then they can
do it for months

00:54:13.820 --> 00:54:19.700
and come back and then take
the tune up a little bit.

00:54:19.700 --> 00:54:26.144
But mostly engineers, fantastic
when it comes to The Happy Body

00:54:26.144 --> 00:54:27.060
measure and following.

00:54:27.060 --> 00:54:27.860
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: We like
things we can measure.

00:54:27.860 --> 00:54:29.120
We're almost out of time.

00:54:29.120 --> 00:54:31.490
One more question from someone?

00:54:31.490 --> 00:54:33.890
Yes.

00:54:33.890 --> 00:54:37.580
AUDIENCE: I just wanted to
ask you again about adherence

00:54:37.580 --> 00:54:41.870
and that if you're a coach,
coaches love athletes,

00:54:41.870 --> 00:54:45.380
because you just give them
a program, and they do it.

00:54:45.380 --> 00:54:46.620
They want to get better.

00:54:46.620 --> 00:54:47.560
They want to succeed.

00:54:47.560 --> 00:54:48.870
They want to win.

00:54:48.870 --> 00:54:54.290
And I think, often, with
non-athletes or normal people,

00:54:54.290 --> 00:54:55.665
even if you have
a great program,

00:54:55.665 --> 00:54:57.248
if you don't stick
to it, you're going

00:54:57.248 --> 00:54:58.370
to get suboptimal results.

00:54:58.370 --> 00:55:01.760
So have there been
any trends or things

00:55:01.760 --> 00:55:03.980
you've noticed when
you work with someone

00:55:03.980 --> 00:55:08.580
about their ability to stick
or not stick with the program?

00:55:08.580 --> 00:55:11.490
Where might someone
relapse, or where might they

00:55:11.490 --> 00:55:12.960
really succeed?

00:55:12.960 --> 00:55:17.460
JERZY GREGOREK: This way,
in the last 10 years,

00:55:17.460 --> 00:55:21.420
we created a lot of
help in that area.

00:55:21.420 --> 00:55:24.870
I wrote three
books of dialogues.

00:55:24.870 --> 00:55:26.520
And I noticed that
we have a dialogue

00:55:26.520 --> 00:55:31.050
in our mind between
fatalist and the master.

00:55:31.050 --> 00:55:33.060
And the dialogue
about the choices.

00:55:33.060 --> 00:55:37.650
And one book is about
dialogues between fatalist

00:55:37.650 --> 00:55:39.225
and the master when
it comes to food.

00:55:39.225 --> 00:55:40.680
The one, exercise.

00:55:40.680 --> 00:55:42.870
And the other one
is about the rest.

00:55:42.870 --> 00:55:44.920
And then there
are 12 situations,

00:55:44.920 --> 00:55:47.910
and there is dialogue between
the fatalist and the master.

00:55:47.910 --> 00:55:54.060
You learn how to hear that
you have those two, first.

00:55:54.060 --> 00:55:57.780
And then you learn how
strong is the fatalist,

00:55:57.780 --> 00:56:00.270
and how strong is
the master, and learn

00:56:00.270 --> 00:56:05.160
how to write down the
situations and write, actually--

00:56:07.740 --> 00:56:11.880
and the dialogue with
the master of 51%.

00:56:11.880 --> 00:56:14.490
So if you can do
that, over time,

00:56:14.490 --> 00:56:16.300
you're actually getting better.

00:56:16.300 --> 00:56:16.800
All right?

00:56:16.800 --> 00:56:21.970
That's the three books of
dialogues that work with it.

00:56:21.970 --> 00:56:25.230
The other book is "I Got This."

00:56:25.230 --> 00:56:28.920
So it's training-- the grit--

00:56:28.920 --> 00:56:33.540
reading stories, reading poems,
and especially written by us.

00:56:33.540 --> 00:56:39.240
So you need to submerge yourself
with people that actually

00:56:39.240 --> 00:56:43.080
do this, also read
stories or watch

00:56:43.080 --> 00:56:47.910
videos and everything that can
help you to stay on the track,

00:56:47.910 --> 00:56:48.840
right?

00:56:48.840 --> 00:56:51.360
Because really,
we don't know what

00:56:51.360 --> 00:56:57.000
words work to a certain
person at a certain time.

00:56:57.000 --> 00:57:01.860
We noticed that after many
years of working with people

00:57:01.860 --> 00:57:05.560
that certain words
work for one person

00:57:05.560 --> 00:57:07.760
but don't work for another one.

00:57:07.760 --> 00:57:11.580
For example, after four years,
that woman came, and she said--

00:57:11.580 --> 00:57:15.880
and I asked her, so
how is it that you

00:57:15.880 --> 00:57:19.870
are able to change this
already for four years

00:57:19.870 --> 00:57:21.610
and then stick to it?

00:57:21.610 --> 00:57:25.250
And she said, you
told me four words.

00:57:25.250 --> 00:57:27.610
And I said, what four words?

00:57:27.610 --> 00:57:30.430
Two years will pass, I told her.

00:57:30.430 --> 00:57:31.940
But I didn't remember.

00:57:31.940 --> 00:57:34.570
But these four words
stuck with her.

00:57:34.570 --> 00:57:38.950
She had the imagination that
the two years will pass,

00:57:38.950 --> 00:57:42.880
and then she will be, in two
years, somewhere in the place,

00:57:42.880 --> 00:57:46.540
and engaged her and
inspired her to do

00:57:46.540 --> 00:57:50.350
the program until the end.

00:57:50.350 --> 00:57:57.660
So I want to close with in
other words, it is time.

00:57:57.660 --> 00:58:05.690
So I met this ballet
dancer who was injured

00:58:05.690 --> 00:58:07.880
and who lost weight.

00:58:07.880 --> 00:58:09.830
And he gained back.

00:58:09.830 --> 00:58:13.190
The brain, 160 and 120.

00:58:13.190 --> 00:58:20.390
So he gained back the
weight after about 10 years.

00:58:20.390 --> 00:58:24.940
I met with him in LA.

00:58:24.940 --> 00:58:27.960
And I said, Barnes, you
have to lose weight.

00:58:27.960 --> 00:58:28.460
Yeah, yeah.

00:58:28.460 --> 00:58:30.660
I have to lose weight.

00:58:30.660 --> 00:58:33.710
And then I said, it is time.

00:58:33.710 --> 00:58:36.480
And Barnes says, yeah, yeah.

00:58:36.480 --> 00:58:38.460
You know when I did.

00:58:38.460 --> 00:58:40.830
I said, Barnes, it is time.

00:58:40.830 --> 00:58:44.220
And Barnes, yes,
but I did it then.

00:58:44.220 --> 00:58:47.320
I said, Barnes, it is time.

00:58:47.320 --> 00:58:49.410
And Barnes looks at me.

00:58:49.410 --> 00:58:50.430
It is time?

00:58:50.430 --> 00:58:51.780
I said, yeah.

00:58:51.780 --> 00:58:53.670
It is time.

00:58:53.670 --> 00:58:58.750
And I said, yeah, it is time.

00:58:58.750 --> 00:58:59.980
And Barnes said, I got it.

00:58:59.980 --> 00:59:00.745
It is time.

00:59:00.745 --> 00:59:01.690
It is time.

00:59:01.690 --> 00:59:05.270
So he goes home, and in
about four or five months,

00:59:05.270 --> 00:59:06.725
loses 50 pounds.

00:59:09.640 --> 00:59:17.530
So we know that somewhere,
the words and the story

00:59:17.530 --> 00:59:21.460
is very motivational
and very powerful

00:59:21.460 --> 00:59:26.530
to do what you need to do.

00:59:26.530 --> 00:59:28.480
So let's say today.

00:59:28.480 --> 00:59:32.800
You could think about what
you want to get better.

00:59:32.800 --> 00:59:35.650
What is the one
thing that you want

00:59:35.650 --> 00:59:41.040
to go home and start improving?

00:59:41.040 --> 00:59:45.830
But if you want to really do
that, you have to pick up one.

00:59:45.830 --> 00:59:46.850
Not two.

00:59:46.850 --> 00:59:47.390
Just one.

00:59:47.390 --> 00:59:50.180
If you want to be
flexible, pick up that one.

00:59:50.180 --> 00:59:52.910
And then start working with it.

00:59:52.910 --> 00:59:55.520
If you want to be strong,
you do the strong.

00:59:55.520 --> 00:59:59.750
If you want to lose
weight, do that.

00:59:59.750 --> 01:00:04.640
But just pick up one and
start really committing to it,

01:00:04.640 --> 01:00:06.380
that you will do it every day.

01:00:06.380 --> 01:00:11.650
And priority, you will
have priority for that one.

01:00:11.650 --> 01:00:15.310
So every day, no matter
what, you will do this,

01:00:15.310 --> 01:00:16.420
and you will do this.

01:00:16.420 --> 01:00:20.204
And you start
improving over time.

01:00:20.204 --> 01:00:21.370
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: All right.

01:00:21.370 --> 01:00:22.411
JERZY GREGOREK: So sorry.

01:00:22.411 --> 01:00:25.309
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

01:00:25.309 --> 01:00:26.350
JERZY GREGOREK: Oh, yeah.

01:00:26.350 --> 01:00:30.280
The hard choices
usually align with--

01:00:30.280 --> 01:00:32.300
hard choices, easy life.

01:00:32.300 --> 01:00:35.630
It's that what you want to
improve, it needs to happen.

01:00:35.630 --> 01:00:38.110
It's like with the stoic.

01:00:38.110 --> 01:00:40.540
It's hard to start to control.

01:00:40.540 --> 01:00:44.250
Something, what will make
you better over time,

01:00:44.250 --> 01:00:47.260
and usually we don't
like it at the beginning.

01:00:47.260 --> 01:00:50.550
So we are the stoic
controlling something,

01:00:50.550 --> 01:00:54.180
but we don't like it.

01:00:54.180 --> 01:01:01.800
And our challenge here is
how to transfer the brain

01:01:01.800 --> 01:01:07.500
toward that goodness that you
want to happen and like it.

01:01:07.500 --> 01:01:11.550
For me it was two potatoes
versus one potato.

01:01:11.550 --> 01:01:14.630
One potato-- I love potatoes.

01:01:14.630 --> 01:01:16.220
I want more potatoes.

01:01:16.220 --> 01:01:18.230
But one potato, I
know, The Happy Body

01:01:18.230 --> 01:01:24.260
tells me one potato is
enough not to get fat.

01:01:24.260 --> 01:01:25.100
OK?

01:01:25.100 --> 01:01:26.790
But I like two potatoes.

01:01:26.790 --> 01:01:29.330
My horse is two
potatoes, three potatoes.

01:01:29.330 --> 01:01:30.530
Not one.

01:01:30.530 --> 01:01:33.300
So after a while, I--

01:01:33.300 --> 01:01:37.570
but I choose one potato
as a stoic, not two.

01:01:37.570 --> 01:01:42.420
But I'm not happy, because
I want two potatoes.

01:01:42.420 --> 01:01:49.050
So my big challenge here
is how to transform myself.

01:01:49.050 --> 01:01:51.080
Transition myself
to the one potato

01:01:51.080 --> 01:01:54.255
and hot to change my believing
system that I actually

01:01:54.255 --> 01:01:57.030
like one potato.

01:01:57.030 --> 01:01:59.850
And that is the happy stoic.

01:01:59.850 --> 01:02:01.260
The happy stoic is that one.

01:02:01.260 --> 01:02:04.050
So today, I will
choose one potato.

01:02:04.050 --> 01:02:05.490
I don't want two potatoes.

01:02:05.490 --> 01:02:06.900
I want one potato.

01:02:06.900 --> 01:02:09.480
But it's the whole
experiences that

01:02:09.480 --> 01:02:15.240
happen throughout the year or
two that build that transition.

01:02:15.240 --> 01:02:16.320
But it is possible.

01:02:16.320 --> 01:02:18.260
And it is really beautiful.

01:02:18.260 --> 01:02:22.890
So when you pick up something,
it will be a hard choice.

01:02:22.890 --> 01:02:25.660
And it will be hard
choice for a while.

01:02:25.660 --> 01:02:28.810
But when you really stick it,
you go home and say, this is--

01:02:28.810 --> 01:02:30.340
I'm going to do it.

01:02:30.340 --> 01:02:34.150
And start working on it
like we work with the dance.

01:02:34.150 --> 01:02:37.000
And even though it's
hard, even though you

01:02:37.000 --> 01:02:39.850
have to wake up
and do it, or you

01:02:39.850 --> 01:02:43.060
pay for it, like we pay for
the dances, it doesn't matter.

01:02:43.060 --> 01:02:45.350
But one thing, not two.

01:02:45.350 --> 01:02:45.850
One.

